cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >
  If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below. The paper
  source of truth is paper/main.md (Markdown) and paper/main.tex (LaTeX);
  both must be kept consistent per repo rule 11.
title: "Obscurity-Is-Dead — AI-Assisted Hacking: Key to Interoperability or Security Nightmare?"
abstract: >
  This paper investigates how modern large language models collapse the
  traditional "effort gap" in reverse engineering. Through two empirical case
  studies (Spider Farmer BLE devices and EcoFlow PowerOcean energy systems)
  plus a third recursive case study of the paper-generation process itself,
  it shows how AI-assisted analysis turns theoretical protocol knowledge into
  practical, replicable local integrations, and proposes a research
  methodology that treats AI conversation transcripts, vendor artifacts, and
  version history as first-class evidence. The dual-use, sloppification, and
  model-collapse risks of AI-assisted research are made explicit and mapped
  to mitigations that the methodology operationalises.
